<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="serious-adj">serious <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'sɪəriəs/    美 /'sɪriəs/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>严重的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a <strong>serious accident</strong> / <strong>illness</strong> / <strong>injury</strong> 
严重的事故/重病/重伤</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Too much packaging is doing <strong>serious damage</strong> to the environment.  
过度包装正在对环境造成严重的损坏。</p><footer>2010 山东</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>重大的；重要的</strong></h4>
<p>important and needing to be thought about carefully：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I have recently got a serious position within my company.  
我最近在公司得到一个重要的职位。</p><footer>2010 全国</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>That sounds a good suggestion. I will give it some <strong>serious thought</strong>. 
那听起来是个好主意，我会认真考虑。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>严肃的；认真的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She looked serious as she told us the bad news. 
她告诉我们这个坏消息时看上去很严肃。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I should not have laughed if I had thought you were serious.  
如果我想到你是认真的，我就不会笑了。</p><footer>2013 江苏</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— I’m going to a party at Carol’s house. 
我要去参加卡罗尔家的聚会。</p><footer>2009 上海</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— <strong>You can’t be serious</strong>. We’ve got two tests at school tomorrow.  
你别开玩笑了，明天我们学校里有两个测验。</p><footer>2009 上海</footer></div>

<h4 id="4">4.<strong>[只用于名词前] 热衷的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I didn’t become a serious climber until the fifth grade.  
我直到五年级才热衷于攀爬。</p><footer>2014 浙江</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>He was wearing a very <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (严肃的) expression and I knew something was wrong.  （2012 陕西）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. serious  </p></div>